## Best Practices

### 1. **Centralize Timing Logic**
âœ… **Good:**
```typescript
// Parent calculates all timing
const activationTime = (index * cycleDuration) / componentCount
bus.emit('activate', { index, delay: activationTime })
```

âŒ **Bad:**
```typescript
// Each child calculates own timing (causes drift)
const myDelay = index * 1000
setTimeout(() => animate(), myDelay)
```

### 2. **Use Event Bus for Cross-Component Communication**
âœ… **Good:**
```typescript
// Parent
bus.emit('pathway-activate', { index: 0 })

// Child
bus.on('pathway-activate', (data) => {
  if (data.index === props.index) animate()
})
```

âŒ **Bad:**
```typescript
// Props drilling through multiple levels
<Parent>
  <Middle @activate="handleActivate">
    <Child @click="$emit('activate')" />
  </Middle>
</Parent>
```

### 3. **Always Clean Up**
âœ… **Good:**
```typescript
const cleanup = bus.on('event', handler)

onUnmounted(() => {
  cleanup()
  bus.cleanup()
  cancelAnimationFrame(animationFrameId)
})
```

âŒ **Bad:**
```typescript
// No cleanup - memory leaks
bus.on('event', handler)
```

### 4. **Respect Performance Constraints**
âœ… **Good:**
```typescript
const { optimizations } = useAnimationEnvironment()

if (optimizations.reducedMotion || optimizations.batteryOptimization) {
  // Skip complex animations
  return
}
```

âŒ **Bad:**
```typescript
// Always run full animation regardless of device state
```

### 5. **Handle Visibility Changes**
âœ… **Good:**
```typescript
const isVisible = useElementVisibility(ref)

watch(isVisible, (visible) => {
  if (!visible) pauseAnimation()
  else if (canStart) resumeAnimation()
})
```

âŒ **Bad:**
```typescript
// Animation runs even when element is offscreen
```

